Gnathopods (Figs 7E, J; 8
A-C
). Carpopropodus of endopod comparatively slender, four times longer than broad in males, versus five times in females; length is 0.8-0.9 times that of merus and 0.9-1.0 times that of ischium in both sexes. Subbasally toothed setae (Fig. 8C): three on carpus plus two in (sub)apical position near outer margin on merus (Fig. 8A, B).
